  "prompt": "What are some good books on Database for beginners?",
  "response": "Here are some highly recommended books on databases for beginners:\n\n1. Introductory Level Books:\n- \"Database Design for Mere Mortals\" by Michael J. Hernandez\n- \"Fundamentals of Database Systems\" by Ramez Elmasri and Shamkant Navathe\n- \"Database Systems: An Application-Oriented Approach\" by Michael Kifer\n\n2. SQL-Specific Books:\n- \"SQL Queries for Mere Mortals\" by John L. Viescas\n- \"Learning SQL\" by Alan Beaulieu\n- \"Head First SQL\" by Lynn Beighley\n\n3. Practical Database Design:\n- \"Database Design and Relational Theory\" by C.J. Date\n- \"Beginning Database Design\" by Clare Churcher\n- \"Database Systems: Design, Implementation, and Management\" by Carlos Coronel\n\n4. NoSQL and Modern Databases:\n- \"MongoDB: The Definitive Guide\" by Shannon Bradshaw\n- \"NoSQL Distilled\" by Pramod J. Sadalage and Martin Fowler\n\n5. Beginner-Friendly Comprehensive Books:\n- \"Designing Data-Intensive Applications\" by Martin Kleppmann\n- \"Database Internals\" by Alex Petrov\n\nEach book offers a different perspective and approach to learning databases.",
